hopobject.body: I'll send you a text maxpharmed.com Many have criticized the Obama administration for belatedly acknowledging that pro-Assad forces inside Syria used chemical weapons against rebels and for not taking the promised action once that red line was crossed. Last month, just prior to meeting with European leaders during the G8 summit, the administration announced it would be sending small arms to help the rebels, but Monday the White House said it would not provide further details on that effort.
